Mexico Stocks: Asur, Cemex, Wal-Mart de Mexico Shares Advance

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-09-06T15:54:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/mexico-stocks-asur-cemex-wal-mart-de-mexico-shares-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:32 a.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 1 percent to 34,211.58.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, gained 1.5 percent to 6.20 pesos. President Barack
Obama said in a speech marking the U.S. Labor Day holiday
yesterday that spending to rebuild the nation’s infrastructure
is a key component of his plan to reignite the economy and boost
hiring.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste SAB (ASURB MM), the
operator of airports in southern Mexico, climbed 3.5 percent to
68.97 pesos. The company’s total passenger traffic jumped 4.2
percent in August from the same period last year, the company
said in a statement distributed by the stock exchange.  Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB (WALMEXV MM), Latin America’s
largest retailer, rose 2.1 percent to 31.77 pesos. The company’s
same-store sales may have climbed 1.2 percent in August,
Citigroup Inc.’s Banamex unit forecast before the report due
today after the market closes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
